1
00:00:09,646 --> 00:00:12,603
The boat was full of weapons.
Rocket launchers, assault rifles.

2
00:00:12,604 --> 00:00:13,895
Military grade. European, I think.

3
00:00:13,896 --> 00:00:15,187
[Fisk] Who knew what was in that ship?

4
00:00:15,188 --> 00:00:17,228
[Buck] Only the Captain
and the First Mate.

5
00:00:17,229 --> 00:00:21,603
The people I work for are very grateful
for the use of your port.

6
00:00:21,604 --> 00:00:25,478
[Matt] If Fisk gets the guns off the boat
into Red Hook, they disappear.

7
00:00:25,479 --> 00:00:27,479
- You know what to do.
- [Karen gasps]

8
00:00:28,063 --> 00:00:29,145
[Daredevil] He killed them all.

9
00:00:29,146 --> 00:00:30,395
[woman on TV] Fisk is tough.

10
00:00:30,396 --> 00:00:32,521
He's getting in the ring this weekend,
isn't he?

11
00:00:34,104 --> 00:00:35,563
Daredevil got away.

12
00:00:37,146 --> 00:00:38,145
- Get in!
- [clamoring]

13
00:00:38,146 --> 00:00:39,853
[Buck] Apparently, someone is helping him.

14
00:00:39,854 --> 00:00:42,562
- [thuds]
- Someone with very good aim.

15
00:00:42,563 --> 00:00:45,854
Have you ever been in the same room
with Benjamin Poindexter?

16
00:00:46,479 --> 00:00:48,103
I have.

17
00:00:48,104 --> 00:00:49,812
[man] Can I help you?

18
00:00:49,813 --> 00:00:50,895
[Dex] Father, I--

19
00:00:50,896 --> 00:00:52,687
I need absolution.

20
00:00:52,688 --> 00:00:53,938
[♪ eerie music playing]

21
00:01:02,896 --> 00:01:05,021
[♪ "New York State of Mind"
by Billy Joel playing]

22
00:01:12,313 --> 00:01:13,396
[stove clicking]

23
00:01:25,479 --> 00:01:27,188
[pan sizzling]

24
00:01:47,438 --> 00:01:49,104
[bones cracking]

25
00:01:54,354 --> 00:01:55,771
[soft cracking]

26
00:01:59,646 --> 00:02:01,812
♪ Some folks like to get away ♪

27
00:02:01,813 --> 00:02:05,854
♪ Take a holiday from the neighborhood ♪

28
00:02:07,646 --> 00:02:12,188
♪ Hop a flight to Miami Beach
or to Hollywood ♪

29
00:02:14,396 --> 00:02:15,937
Ah, Tony.

30
00:02:15,938 --> 00:02:17,854
Good morning, Mrs. Smithers.

31
00:02:18,938 --> 00:02:21,313
- [Mrs. Smithers] Aw! [chuckles]
- [meows]

32
00:02:24,021 --> 00:02:27,563
♪ I'm in a New York state of mind ♪

33
00:02:28,938 --> 00:02:31,187
Such a nice boy.

34
00:02:31,188 --> 00:02:32,646
Have a nice day.

35
00:02:34,271 --> 00:02:36,062
[whistling "New York State of Mind"]

36
00:02:36,063 --> 00:02:38,478
♪ I've seen all the movie stars ♪

37
00:02:38,479 --> 00:02:42,228
♪ In their fancy cars
and their limousines ♪

38
00:02:42,229 --> 00:02:43,603
[continues whistling]

39
00:02:43,604 --> 00:02:46,187
- [coin clinks]
- [coins jingling]

40
00:02:46,188 --> 00:02:48,604
♪ Under the evergreens ♪

41
00:02:51,604 --> 00:02:53,770
♪ I know what I'm needing ♪

42
00:02:53,771 --> 00:02:55,521
[bell dinging]

43
00:02:59,771 --> 00:03:00,896
[soft chattering]

44
00:03:12,563 --> 00:03:13,854
[sighs]

45
00:03:27,854 --> 00:03:29,271
You ready?

46
00:03:30,271 --> 00:03:32,063
What are you famous for?

47
00:03:32,646 --> 00:03:36,813
[sighs] I mean, the milkshakes are good.

48
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:38,728
- Excellent.
- [waitress] Mm-hmm.

49
00:03:38,729 --> 00:03:40,021
I'll have, uh...

50
00:03:41,438 --> 00:03:43,770
- one banana milkshake.
- [waitress scribbling]

51
00:03:43,771 --> 00:03:45,438
You want whip?

52
00:03:46,813 --> 00:03:48,396
Doesn't everybody?

53
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,770
[sighs]

54
00:03:50,771 --> 00:03:52,771
[♪ soft jazz music playing over speaker]

55
00:04:12,729 --> 00:04:14,854
[machine whirs]

56
00:04:21,271 --> 00:04:23,103
[operator] Task Force hotline.
What's your emergency?

57
00:04:23,104 --> 00:04:25,770
I think I just saw Frank Castle

58
00:04:25,771 --> 00:04:29,145
enter Bel Aire Diner at 43rd and 10th.

59
00:04:29,146 --> 00:04:30,312
[operator] The Punisher?

60
00:04:30,313 --> 00:04:31,395
Are you sure?

61
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:32,771
Oh, yeah.

62
00:04:33,271 --> 00:04:34,562
Yeah, it's him.

63
00:04:34,563 --> 00:04:35,895
[operator] Task force is en route.

64
00:04:35,896 --> 00:04:37,145
Shit.

65
00:04:37,146 --> 00:04:38,729
He has a gun.

66
00:04:39,479 --> 00:04:40,853
- Try to find a safe place--
- [phone beeps]

67
00:04:40,854 --> 00:04:42,438
[whirring]

68
00:04:52,854 --> 00:04:54,188
[hissing]

69
00:05:00,813 --> 00:05:02,062
[waitress] There you go.

70
00:05:02,063 --> 00:05:03,313
Thank you.

71
00:05:14,938 --> 00:05:16,188
[sucking]

72
00:05:22,688 --> 00:05:24,896
- [slurps]
- [sirens approaching]

73
00:05:34,813 --> 00:05:37,063
[sirens blaring]

74
00:05:38,854 --> 00:05:39,937
[officer] Entry team get prepped.

75
00:05:39,938 --> 00:05:41,103
Let's do it. Let's get...

76
00:05:41,104 --> 00:05:42,603
- On your six!
- [officer 2] On me, on me!

77
00:05:42,604 --> 00:05:44,271
[officers shouting indistinctly]

78
00:05:45,271 --> 00:05:46,478
[officer] Everybody, stay in your seats!

79
00:05:46,479 --> 00:05:47,895
- Keep your hands up!
- [officer 2] Hey! Hey!

80
00:05:47,896 --> 00:05:49,603
- [officer 3] Everyone, sit down!
- [officer 2] Don't move!

81
00:05:49,604 --> 00:05:51,937
- [officer 4] Nobody leaves! Nobody leaves!
- [officer 5] Throw 'em down!

82
00:05:51,938 --> 00:05:53,520
- Down!
- [clamoring]

83
00:05:53,521 --> 00:05:54,979
- [officer 4] Let's go!
- Stay down!

84
00:05:56,521 --> 00:05:58,145
- [officer 4] Nobody fucking move.
- [officer 3] You got eyes?

85
00:05:58,146 --> 00:05:59,853
- I got nothin'.
- [officer 4] What's in the back?

86
00:05:59,854 --> 00:06:01,187
- [officer 6] Clear!
- [officer 4] Max?

87
00:06:01,188 --> 00:06:02,271
[officer 7] Clear!

88
00:06:03,854 --> 00:06:05,270
[officer 4] Yo!

89
00:06:05,271 --> 00:06:06,354
Milkshake!

90
00:06:07,396 --> 00:06:08,853
Put your goddamn hands up.

91
00:06:08,854 --> 00:06:10,146
Turn around now.

92
00:06:10,646 --> 00:06:11,896
Let's go!

93
00:06:14,229 --> 00:06:16,020
[chair squeaks]

94
00:06:16,021 --> 00:06:17,103
[softly] What...

95
00:06:17,104 --> 00:06:18,562
- [blows]
- [grunts]

96
00:06:18,563 --> 00:06:20,562
[♪ "New York State of Mind"
by Billy Joel continues]

97
00:06:20,563 --> 00:06:23,270
[officers grunting]

98
00:06:23,271 --> 00:06:24,688
[Bullseye grunts]

99
00:06:25,479 --> 00:06:27,145
[both grunting]

100
00:06:27,146 --> 00:06:28,896
- [officer 8] Stop resisting!
- [officer 9] Now!

101
00:06:30,188 --> 00:06:31,813
[Bullseye grunts]

102
00:06:34,396 --> 00:06:36,854
♪ I don't have any reasons ♪

103
00:06:37,313 --> 00:06:38,728
[waitress groaning]

104
00:06:38,729 --> 00:06:40,228
♪ I left them all behind ♪

105
00:06:40,229 --> 00:06:42,521
- [Bullseye grunting]
- [utensil stabs]

106
00:06:44,063 --> 00:06:45,521
[Bullseye] That was a great milkshake.

107
00:06:47,063 --> 00:06:49,646
[gurgling, choking]

108
00:06:50,729 --> 00:06:51,896
[screams in pain]

109
00:06:53,229 --> 00:06:56,563
[Bullseye grunting]

110
00:06:58,896 --> 00:07:00,396
[gasps]

111
00:07:03,063 --> 00:07:05,729
[grunting]

112
00:07:07,646 --> 00:07:09,895
- [dog barking]
- [Bullseye] Huh?

113
00:07:09,896 --> 00:07:11,687
- [grunts]
- [dog barks]

114
00:07:11,688 --> 00:07:13,104
[whines]

115
00:07:23,021 --> 00:07:25,729
Dogs in restaurants are unsanitary.

116
00:07:27,313 --> 00:07:28,687
[voice shaking] Please don't...

117
00:07:28,688 --> 00:07:29,813
kill me.

118
00:07:32,938 --> 00:07:34,938
[breathing heavily, grunting]

119
00:07:35,563 --> 00:07:37,063
Oh, don't worry.

120
00:07:37,854 --> 00:07:40,521
[screams, groans]

121
00:07:41,854 --> 00:07:43,353
I'm one of the good guys.

122
00:07:43,354 --> 00:07:45,270
♪ I'm just taking a Greyhound ♪

123
00:07:45,271 --> 00:07:46,395
[whines]

124
00:07:46,396 --> 00:07:47,895
♪ On the Hudson River Line ♪

125
00:07:47,896 --> 00:07:49,478
[man over radio] Negative.
Can we know get an...

126
00:07:49,479 --> 00:07:50,813
It's fucking Bullseye!

127
00:07:51,729 --> 00:07:53,688
It's Bullseye! It's-- [grunts]

128
00:07:57,396 --> 00:07:58,396
[chuckles]

129
00:07:58,979 --> 00:07:59,978
[whines]

130
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:01,854
♪ 'Cause I'm in ♪

131
00:08:06,896 --> 00:08:09,103
♪ I'm in a New York ♪

132
00:08:09,104 --> 00:08:11,603
[ketchup bottle squirts]

133
00:08:11,604 --> 00:08:17,520
♪ State of mind ♪

134
00:08:17,521 --> 00:08:18,938
[doorbell dinging]

135
00:08:19,563 --> 00:08:23,479
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

136
00:08:36,354 --> 00:08:38,438
[♪ theme music playing]

137
00:10:17,396 --> 00:10:19,395
[City Without Fear voice] It's me again.

138
00:10:19,396 --> 00:10:21,312
A cringe explosion in the East River?

139
00:10:21,313 --> 00:10:22,853
Don't worry about it!

140
00:10:22,854 --> 00:10:24,103
Floating dead bodies?

141
00:10:24,104 --> 00:10:25,770
Don't worry about it.

142
00:10:25,771 --> 00:10:29,520
All smoke and mirrors,
distracting you from the main event!

143
00:10:29,521 --> 00:10:31,437
- My charity boxing match...
- [bell dings]

144
00:10:31,438 --> 00:10:35,270
...that's raising money for a New York
Born Again revitalization project,

145
00:10:35,271 --> 00:10:36,812
that is really a shell corporation
for money laundering

146
00:10:36,813 --> 00:10:38,978
to offshore accounts
that make my friends grotesquely rich.

147
00:10:38,979 --> 00:10:40,187
[breathing heavily]

148
00:10:40,188 --> 00:10:44,103
I've been training hard at the gym
for you, New York.

149
00:10:44,104 --> 00:10:45,728
The money we will raise will go to

150
00:10:45,729 --> 00:10:46,812
arresting you without due process,

151
00:10:46,813 --> 00:10:48,020
seizing your property
for my personal gain,

152
00:10:48,021 --> 00:10:50,103
locking up your loved ones,
and so much more.

153
00:10:50,104 --> 00:10:52,645
Back to the gym, I go, because

154
00:10:52,646 --> 00:10:55,229
I love you, New York!

155
00:10:55,771 --> 00:10:58,187
[horns blaring distantly]

156
00:10:58,188 --> 00:11:01,104
[officer] We're getting split
by coordinates. Nothing to report.

157
00:11:02,771 --> 00:11:05,228
[Soledad] My name is Soledad Ayala.

158
00:11:05,229 --> 00:11:07,978
I am a nurse from Washington Heights.

159
00:11:07,979 --> 00:11:10,520
I was arrested by the Task Force,

160
00:11:10,521 --> 00:11:13,354
the same people who killed my husband.

161
00:11:14,313 --> 00:11:15,313
I am the missing.

162
00:11:16,604 --> 00:11:17,854
But I will not back down.

163
00:11:18,938 --> 00:11:19,938
I will stay...

164
00:11:20,646 --> 00:11:21,688
and fight.

165
00:11:22,563 --> 00:11:25,062
- [device beeps]
- [Karen] It's okay. Thank you.

166
00:11:25,063 --> 00:11:26,603
[Jack] It's time for me to go.

167
00:11:26,604 --> 00:11:28,145
I wish you'd reconsider.

168
00:11:28,146 --> 00:11:31,770
[chuckles] I have been
in a cage for... [sighs]

169
00:11:31,771 --> 00:11:33,770
...six months.

170
00:11:33,771 --> 00:11:37,062
I need to shower.
I need to burn these clothes. [sighs]

171
00:11:37,063 --> 00:11:38,562
I'm too old for this shit.

172
00:11:38,563 --> 00:11:41,313
Ah, it's a shame 'cause we could use
more people like you.

173
00:11:42,479 --> 00:11:43,479
Like me?

174
00:11:45,354 --> 00:11:46,813
You don't realize it, do you?

175
00:11:47,979 --> 00:11:49,271
You're not a hero.

176
00:11:50,271 --> 00:11:51,853
You're a symbol now.

177
00:11:51,854 --> 00:11:53,771
Hope for an entire city.

178
00:11:55,688 --> 00:11:56,688
It's true.

179
00:11:57,563 --> 00:11:59,270
I gave Karen an account number.

180
00:11:59,271 --> 00:12:00,937
Use whatever you need,

181
00:12:00,938 --> 00:12:02,103
whenever you need it.

182
00:12:02,104 --> 00:12:03,312
Thank you.

183
00:12:03,313 --> 00:12:04,771
Good luck, my friend.

184
00:12:05,854 --> 00:12:07,563
- Destroy them both.
- [chuckles]

185
00:12:11,979 --> 00:12:13,645
- [Angela] Hey.
- Hey.

186
00:12:13,646 --> 00:12:14,895
What you got there?

187
00:12:14,896 --> 00:12:17,603
Uh, SD card.
I'm supposed to get it to my source,

188
00:12:17,604 --> 00:12:18,853
but with the Task Force everywhere,

189
00:12:18,854 --> 00:12:20,438
- I'm too exposed.
- It's okay.

190
00:12:21,271 --> 00:12:22,520
Let me do it.

191
00:12:22,521 --> 00:12:25,646
- [chuckles] Absolutely not.
- Oh, come on.

192
00:12:26,563 --> 00:12:29,563
[whispering] No, come on, I just need
to do this for my aunt, please.

193
00:12:31,188 --> 00:12:33,688
[sighs] No way. It's too dangerous.

194
00:12:34,646 --> 00:12:35,645
So what?

195
00:12:35,646 --> 00:12:37,062
I stole their truck.

196
00:12:37,063 --> 00:12:39,853
[whispering] They're probably already
looking for me. [chuckles softly]

197
00:12:39,854 --> 00:12:41,813
[♪ tense music playing]

198
00:12:45,104 --> 00:12:46,354
[Karen sighs]

199
00:12:50,688 --> 00:12:51,770
Thank you.

200
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:52,979
Be careful.

201
00:13:02,438 --> 00:13:03,438
[inhales sharply]

202
00:13:05,896 --> 00:13:06,938
[sighs]

203
00:13:07,896 --> 00:13:09,354
[soft clinking]

204
00:13:12,604 --> 00:13:14,938
Do you understand the responsibility
that comes with this?

205
00:13:16,563 --> 00:13:17,603
Yeah,

206
00:13:17,604 --> 00:13:18,729
I do.

207
00:13:19,854 --> 00:13:20,979
Are you ready?

208
00:13:22,313 --> 00:13:23,313
[chuckles]

209
00:13:24,271 --> 00:13:25,271
Were you?

210
00:13:25,771 --> 00:13:27,478
[rumbling]

211
00:13:27,479 --> 00:13:29,521
- [heart thumping]
- [heavy breathing]

212
00:13:30,479 --> 00:13:31,896
[whispering] Everybody, stay still.

213
00:13:40,354 --> 00:13:42,729
- [thumping continues]
- [♪ tense music playing]

214
00:13:47,313 --> 00:13:48,438
[creaking]

215
00:13:49,896 --> 00:13:51,854
[man yells, grunts]

216
00:13:53,479 --> 00:13:55,937
[gasps] My name is Christofi Savva.

217
00:13:55,938 --> 00:13:57,478
I'm here to help. [gasps]

218
00:13:57,479 --> 00:13:59,979
I was the First Mate on the Northern Star.

219
00:14:01,063 --> 00:14:02,604
[breathes heavily]

220
00:14:10,271 --> 00:14:11,271
[kisses]

221
00:14:11,896 --> 00:14:14,104
That's one way to deal with the Governor.

222
00:14:15,979 --> 00:14:17,270
It's for the journey,

223
00:14:17,271 --> 00:14:18,353
not the meeting.

224
00:14:18,354 --> 00:14:20,563
Marge and I have a rapport.

225
00:14:23,438 --> 00:14:25,396
And I appreciate you talkin' to her.

226
00:14:27,146 --> 00:14:28,563
I know what you're doing.

227
00:14:29,854 --> 00:14:31,228
Arranging this

228
00:14:31,229 --> 00:14:33,604
trip to Albany just before the fight.

229
00:14:35,854 --> 00:14:37,146
I don't like it...

230
00:14:38,479 --> 00:14:40,729
when you send me away and shut me out.

231
00:14:42,646 --> 00:14:44,020
This is not that.

232
00:14:44,021 --> 00:14:45,688
It's a public place.

233
00:14:47,813 --> 00:14:49,938
Too much could go wrong.

234
00:14:52,479 --> 00:14:54,188
We're a matched set.

235
00:14:54,729 --> 00:14:56,313
I should be there tonight.

236
00:15:00,271 --> 00:15:01,896
I'll call you when it's over.

237
00:15:03,604 --> 00:15:05,271
[inhales deeply]

238
00:15:10,438 --> 00:15:13,229
[♪ eerie music playing]

239
00:15:31,521 --> 00:15:32,604
Good luck.

240
00:15:40,313 --> 00:15:43,479
[door opens, shuts]

241
00:15:44,354 --> 00:15:46,729
[Christofi] You were captured
only for helping me.

242
00:15:49,604 --> 00:15:51,646
I would like to return that kindness.

243
00:15:54,104 --> 00:15:56,521
What can you tell us
about the Northern Star?

244
00:15:58,021 --> 00:15:59,104
Everything.

245
00:16:00,063 --> 00:16:02,271
The illegal weapons, the fake documents...

246
00:16:05,979 --> 00:16:08,563
Can you connect any of it to Fisk?

247
00:16:12,104 --> 00:16:13,396
We were protected.

248
00:16:14,063 --> 00:16:16,896
All the paperwork was signed off by...

249
00:16:18,146 --> 00:16:19,688
Vasillias tou Enklimatos.

250
00:16:21,229 --> 00:16:22,646
The Kingpin.

251
00:16:29,396 --> 00:16:31,646
Well, we need an attorney
to take his statement.

252
00:16:33,563 --> 00:16:35,270
- [sighs] Kirsten...
- Yeah, yeah.

253
00:16:35,271 --> 00:16:36,687
Well, it's too dangerous
to bring Christofi to her,

254
00:16:36,688 --> 00:16:38,062
so she'll have to come to us.

255
00:16:38,063 --> 00:16:40,562
Won't be too hard. All the Task Force
will be at the fight tonight.

256
00:16:40,563 --> 00:16:41,895
Yeah, yeah.

257
00:16:41,896 --> 00:16:43,396
At Fogwell's.

258
00:16:46,563 --> 00:16:48,688
Some of the last memories
of my father are in that gym.

259
00:16:49,563 --> 00:16:51,688
[sighs] Now, it's crawling
with Task Force.

260
00:16:52,521 --> 00:16:53,854
Yeah, he wants me there.

261
00:16:54,354 --> 00:16:57,063
- [inhales deeply]
- Or...

262
00:16:57,938 --> 00:16:59,103
Not just me.

263
00:16:59,104 --> 00:17:00,228
The whole fight--

264
00:17:00,229 --> 00:17:01,563
He's setting a trap for Bullseye.

265
00:17:02,313 --> 00:17:03,563
[sighs] Oh, fuck.

266
00:17:05,354 --> 00:17:07,103
- [grunts] I'm gonna find Bullseye.
- Mm-hmm.

267
00:17:07,104 --> 00:17:09,062
- You just connect Kirsten and Christofi.
- Christofi.

268
00:17:09,063 --> 00:17:10,312
Yep. [sighs]

269
00:17:10,313 --> 00:17:12,188
- All right. Be careful.
- You, too.

270
00:17:15,146 --> 00:17:16,271
I love you.

271
00:17:19,188 --> 00:17:20,396
I love you, too.

272
00:17:24,479 --> 00:17:26,145
[reporter] I'm here outside Fogwell's Gym,

273
00:17:26,146 --> 00:17:30,562
a part of Mayor Fisk's Born Again
revitalization project,

274
00:17:30,563 --> 00:17:32,978
and host to tonight's benefit boxing match

275
00:17:32,979 --> 00:17:34,937
between the Mayor and heavyweight

276
00:17:34,938 --> 00:17:36,937
Mike "the Matterhorn" Melendez.

277
00:17:36,938 --> 00:17:39,312
Due to the recent spate
of vigilante violence,

278
00:17:39,313 --> 00:17:40,937
I'm told security will be tight,

279
00:17:40,938 --> 00:17:43,188
- with increased Task Force to--
- [shatters]

280
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:45,645
[Kirsten] No, I don't understand.

281
00:17:45,646 --> 00:17:48,563
I was under the impression
that that account was paid in full.

282
00:17:49,729 --> 00:17:51,645
[shouting] Down on the fucking ground now!

283
00:17:51,646 --> 00:17:54,478
Down on the fucking ground!
Out of your fucking chairs! Down!

284
00:17:54,479 --> 00:17:56,270
- On the fucking ground! Down!
- [Kirsten] Hey! Hey!

285
00:17:56,271 --> 00:17:59,978
You assholes better have a warrant, or
I'm gonna bury you under so many lawsuits

286
00:17:59,979 --> 00:18:03,812
that your grandchildren's grandchildren
will still be paying your legal bills.

287
00:18:03,813 --> 00:18:05,062
- Safer Streets.
- [objects clattering]

288
00:18:05,063 --> 00:18:08,271
- I don't need a warrant or probable cause.
- We won't even need to knock.

289
00:18:09,021 --> 00:18:10,021
You again?

290
00:18:11,146 --> 00:18:12,770
- [Powell] Where's your client?
- [Kirsten] Which one?

291
00:18:12,771 --> 00:18:15,187
[Powell] Terrorist fugitive Jack Duquesne,
also known as Swordsman.

292
00:18:15,188 --> 00:18:18,063
- Allegedly.
- A court of law found him guilty.

293
00:18:18,688 --> 00:18:19,854
That was no court.

294
00:18:20,354 --> 00:18:22,187
Whatever.
I'm not gonna fucking ask you again.

295
00:18:22,188 --> 00:18:23,645
Do you see him here? Anywhere?

296
00:18:23,646 --> 00:18:27,187
Maybe he's hiding under a pile of files
or that wall made of glass.

297
00:18:27,188 --> 00:18:28,313
Nothing, sir.

298
00:18:29,771 --> 00:18:31,020
You hear from him, you turn him in.

299
00:18:31,021 --> 00:18:32,895
Attorney-client privilege still applies.

300
00:18:32,896 --> 00:18:35,687
I don't give a fuck about your
attorney-client whatever the fuck.

301
00:18:35,688 --> 00:18:37,770
He was part of a terrorist attack
that killed 25 men

302
00:18:37,771 --> 00:18:39,354
- on board that ship.
- Bullshit.

303
00:18:39,938 --> 00:18:41,145
Talk like that will get you hurt someday.

304
00:18:41,146 --> 00:18:43,188
Talk like that is how I do my fucking job.

305
00:18:45,896 --> 00:18:48,563
You tell Matt Murdock we said hello. Okay?

306
00:18:52,688 --> 00:18:53,771
See you around, Counselor!

307
00:18:55,271 --> 00:18:56,271
[clatters]

308
00:18:59,604 --> 00:19:01,645
[Fisk] First, Bullseye and now this.

309
00:19:01,646 --> 00:19:02,978
And how many escaped?

310
00:19:02,979 --> 00:19:04,438
Nineteen in total.

311
00:19:04,896 --> 00:19:06,771
[sighs] I've had enough!

312
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:10,353
There's leaks in Red Hook,
leaks in City Hall!

313
00:19:10,354 --> 00:19:11,812
You need to find them, Buck!

314
00:19:11,813 --> 00:19:13,228
Plug them!

315
00:19:13,229 --> 00:19:14,396
Every one!

316
00:19:15,771 --> 00:19:17,520
- How much you wanna know?
- Enough to know what's--

317
00:19:17,521 --> 00:19:18,771
[Charles] You know what I wanna know?

318
00:19:19,396 --> 00:19:20,645
Why... [munching]

319
00:19:20,646 --> 00:19:22,729
...is wombat shit cube-shaped?

320
00:19:23,521 --> 00:19:25,188
I mean, it's the strangest thing
I've ever seen.

321
00:19:26,063 --> 00:19:28,520
Apparently, they like to
stack it into, like,

322
00:19:28,521 --> 00:19:32,478
little walls that mark
their territory. [laughs]

323
00:19:32,479 --> 00:19:33,645
Isn't that weird?

324
00:19:33,646 --> 00:19:36,895
Little Lego walls of wombat shit

325
00:19:36,896 --> 00:19:38,145
to get the bitches.

326
00:19:38,146 --> 00:19:39,479
They literally shit bricks.

327
00:19:40,938 --> 00:19:44,228
Charles, you are not on my agenda.

328
00:19:44,229 --> 00:19:47,271
I have another awesome
existential question.

329
00:19:48,146 --> 00:19:50,395
Why is my non-cube shitting ass

330
00:19:50,396 --> 00:19:52,728
sitting on a pile of HK 416s

331
00:19:52,729 --> 00:19:56,437
and rocket launchers,
and other assorted weapons, when this,

332
00:19:56,438 --> 00:19:59,603
all of this, is not supposed to be
in a warehouse in Brooklyn.

333
00:19:59,604 --> 00:20:03,312
It's supposed to be on its way to
Guinea-Bissau to win the hearts and minds.

334
00:20:03,313 --> 00:20:05,729
Because Daredevil knows it's in New York.

335
00:20:06,438 --> 00:20:07,563
[Charles] People need these arms.

336
00:20:08,104 --> 00:20:09,771
Shots must be fired.

337
00:20:10,688 --> 00:20:12,770
If you put these on another boat,

338
00:20:12,771 --> 00:20:15,770
we'll have the Northern Star
all over again, or worse.

339
00:20:15,771 --> 00:20:19,145
And I don't need my city
turning on me. Not now.

340
00:20:19,146 --> 00:20:21,395
Your city. [laughs]

341
00:20:21,396 --> 00:20:23,187
- That's rich.
- Do not mock me!

342
00:20:23,188 --> 00:20:25,687
It is a big world out there, sailor.

343
00:20:25,688 --> 00:20:30,520
With big wars and much, much bigger stakes
than one elected official.

344
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:32,978
Official who gave you access
to an American free port.

345
00:20:32,979 --> 00:20:35,478
And on behalf of the agency,
we appreciate your service.

346
00:20:35,479 --> 00:20:38,854
A service, I might remind you,
which is yet to be rendered.

347
00:20:39,479 --> 00:20:41,563
I will honor our arrangement.

348
00:20:42,229 --> 00:20:43,353
Well, that's great.

349
00:20:43,354 --> 00:20:45,728
I mean, the question kind of becomes
"Can you?" Right?

350
00:20:45,729 --> 00:20:49,520
I mean, you've been rocking and rolling
with all your big cat friends.

351
00:20:49,521 --> 00:20:52,937
And then Uncle Sam shows up,
and your facility, the...

352
00:20:52,938 --> 00:20:57,187
the golden fucking goose is cooked
because this place is compromised.

353
00:20:57,188 --> 00:21:00,395
And your Governor is threatening
to revoke its charter.

354
00:21:00,396 --> 00:21:02,187
You are overreaching.

355
00:21:02,188 --> 00:21:03,812
[Charles] From where I'm sitting,

356
00:21:03,813 --> 00:21:05,603
it seems to me you're having a--

357
00:21:05,604 --> 00:21:09,396
[grunts] Just a very difficult time
controlling...

358
00:21:10,104 --> 00:21:13,103
your very, very small piece of the world.

359
00:21:13,104 --> 00:21:14,729
I am not your employee!

360
00:21:15,646 --> 00:21:17,021
[breathes deeply]

361
00:21:18,604 --> 00:21:19,688
I never said you were.

362
00:21:20,479 --> 00:21:23,812
Partners, Wilson--
Come on! We're partners.

363
00:21:23,813 --> 00:21:25,978
Hey, I don't respond well to threats.

364
00:21:25,979 --> 00:21:27,354
[chuckling] That's not a threat.

365
00:21:29,438 --> 00:21:31,062
Look, neither of us ever walk in anywhere

366
00:21:31,063 --> 00:21:33,478
without knowing how we're gonna get out.

367
00:21:33,479 --> 00:21:36,229
[chuckles] It's adorable,
but you can put your hands down.

368
00:21:37,229 --> 00:21:38,313
You're right.

369
00:21:38,938 --> 00:21:41,479
- [officers grunt]
- [bodies thudding]

370
00:21:43,396 --> 00:21:46,646
[Fisk] Your shipment will be delivered
when the time is right.

371
00:21:47,188 --> 00:21:49,688
I would ask that you practice patience!

372
00:21:53,729 --> 00:21:55,604
Next time you wanna see me, call.

373
00:21:57,313 --> 00:21:58,313
It's courteous.

374
00:22:05,479 --> 00:22:08,104
- [door shuts]
- Shit.

375
00:22:09,188 --> 00:22:10,728
This was retaliation,

376
00:22:10,729 --> 00:22:13,062
and then our accounts
are mysteriously frozen.

377
00:22:13,063 --> 00:22:14,437
It's not a coincidence.

378
00:22:14,438 --> 00:22:15,937
I wouldn't be here if it wasn't important.

379
00:22:15,938 --> 00:22:17,145
Yeah. Well, the last time I helped you,

380
00:22:17,146 --> 00:22:19,353
I ended up as an accessory
to a terrorist attack.

381
00:22:19,354 --> 00:22:22,188
Well, and Fisk sunk that ship.
Not Daredevil.

382
00:22:27,271 --> 00:22:28,354
Where's Matt?

383
00:22:28,896 --> 00:22:29,896
Karen?

384
00:22:33,063 --> 00:22:35,854
[sighs] Can't answer that...

385
00:22:36,813 --> 00:22:37,854
but he's safe.

386
00:22:40,604 --> 00:22:41,646
Okay.

387
00:22:43,729 --> 00:22:45,313
You think you know people...

388
00:22:55,229 --> 00:22:56,229
Here.

389
00:22:58,396 --> 00:22:59,438
Thanks.

390
00:23:03,896 --> 00:23:05,146
You do, you know.

391
00:23:13,146 --> 00:23:14,604
All right. [sighs]

392
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:20,729
What do you need? And how much
is it gonna screw with my life?

393
00:23:22,521 --> 00:23:23,688
[chuckles softly]

394
00:23:25,313 --> 00:23:27,728
[Governor] To be honest,
I was expecting the call.

395
00:23:27,729 --> 00:23:29,854
I just wasn't expecting it from you.

396
00:23:30,688 --> 00:23:33,479
It's not often I'm surprised. [sighs]

397
00:23:34,563 --> 00:23:37,603
[Vanessa] You and I speak
a more similar language than my husband.

398
00:23:37,604 --> 00:23:39,396
[Governor] The Mayor, I understand.

399
00:23:40,188 --> 00:23:42,521
It's you, that's the mystery to me.

400
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:46,438
Now, he... he's like the White Bull,
crashing through everything.

401
00:23:47,104 --> 00:23:48,478
Does that make you Europa?

402
00:23:48,479 --> 00:23:51,395
Oh. I'm no victim.

403
00:23:51,396 --> 00:23:53,063
I'm not entirely sure she was either.

404
00:23:54,146 --> 00:23:58,145
[breathes deeply] We can be candid
with each other, right?

405
00:23:58,146 --> 00:23:59,813
Of course, that's why I'm here.

406
00:24:01,438 --> 00:24:03,729
I don't like the way your husband
wields his power.

407
00:24:04,479 --> 00:24:05,812
I don't trust it,

408
00:24:05,813 --> 00:24:07,438
and it makes me nervous.

409
00:24:08,229 --> 00:24:09,979
I don't see Safer Streets,

410
00:24:10,521 --> 00:24:12,437
a thriving economy, and...

411
00:24:12,438 --> 00:24:14,813
neighborhood revitalization as problems.

412
00:24:15,438 --> 00:24:16,771
"New York Born Again."

413
00:24:17,521 --> 00:24:20,062
- A bit grandiose, don't you think?
- [both chuckle]

414
00:24:20,063 --> 00:24:23,438
My husband has big plans
for the city he loves.

415
00:24:25,604 --> 00:24:27,938
It'd be a shame if New York's progress

416
00:24:28,771 --> 00:24:32,354
was halted because of
unfortunate decisions.

417
00:24:33,354 --> 00:24:35,270
I said the Mayor gives me pause.

418
00:24:35,271 --> 00:24:36,520
You don't.

419
00:24:36,521 --> 00:24:40,187
The city shuts down businesses,
you unload them to Cooper and others,

420
00:24:40,188 --> 00:24:42,937
laying down the infrastructure
for long-term growth.

421
00:24:42,938 --> 00:24:44,313
It's shrewd...

422
00:24:45,438 --> 00:24:46,812
and ruthless.

423
00:24:46,813 --> 00:24:48,563
And I mean that as a compliment.

424
00:24:49,146 --> 00:24:50,563
I take it as one.

425
00:24:51,479 --> 00:24:52,563
Thank you.

426
00:24:53,188 --> 00:24:56,604
You could have done all of this
on your own.

427
00:24:57,438 --> 00:25:01,021
And yet, you chose to do it with Wilson.

428
00:25:02,146 --> 00:25:03,146
Why?

429
00:25:08,354 --> 00:25:09,770
I never thought it'd be him.

430
00:25:09,771 --> 00:25:11,479
[♪ eerie music playing]

431
00:25:12,771 --> 00:25:13,771
And then it was.

432
00:25:15,896 --> 00:25:18,104
And now I can't imagine it...

433
00:25:20,854 --> 00:25:22,104
being any other way.

434
00:25:24,979 --> 00:25:27,771
Can you temper his darker impulses?

435
00:25:29,979 --> 00:25:32,937
You want guarantees that I can't give you,

436
00:25:32,938 --> 00:25:34,688
but I can give you this...

437
00:25:35,438 --> 00:25:38,271
my husband loves New York,
and I love my husband.

438
00:25:39,854 --> 00:25:42,479
And I know how to bring out
the very best in him.

439
00:25:45,104 --> 00:25:47,145
Honestly, I... I couldn't sleep at night

440
00:25:47,146 --> 00:25:48,646
backing Mayor Fisk.

441
00:25:53,229 --> 00:25:56,438
But I can back Mayor and Mrs. Fisk.

442
00:25:59,146 --> 00:26:00,271
Thank you.

443
00:26:04,438 --> 00:26:05,813
- Thank you.
- Okay.

444
00:26:06,396 --> 00:26:09,020
Uh, we ran out of guac, bro,
but shit's still gonna be bussin'.

445
00:26:09,021 --> 00:26:11,353
[♪ hip-hop song playing
over speaker]

446
00:26:11,354 --> 00:26:14,312
Uh, welcome to Arriba Arepas.

447
00:26:14,313 --> 00:26:15,437
What do you want?

448
00:26:15,438 --> 00:26:17,354
Una arepa paisa, por favor.

449
00:26:19,188 --> 00:26:20,978
Oh, my gosh. A leprechaun.

450
00:26:20,979 --> 00:26:23,438
- Did you lose your pot of gold?
- Just shut the fuck up, Javi.

451
00:26:25,479 --> 00:26:27,229
I need you to do something for me.

452
00:26:28,229 --> 00:26:29,313
Fuck is this?

453
00:26:30,938 --> 00:26:32,896
I need you not to screw it up.

454
00:26:33,438 --> 00:26:35,188
Chill, I got you.

455
00:26:35,854 --> 00:26:37,645
I will seriously beat your ass.

456
00:26:37,646 --> 00:26:39,395
Ay, ay!

457
00:26:39,396 --> 00:26:40,646
You don't want that arepa?

458
00:26:41,438 --> 00:26:42,479
I... I guess not.

459
00:26:44,229 --> 00:26:46,396
Yeah, I'm not taking customers right now.
Give me one second.

460
00:26:47,563 --> 00:26:48,688
[doorbell dinging]

461
00:26:58,313 --> 00:26:59,479
[squeaks]

462
00:27:01,438 --> 00:27:02,895
All right, wrap it up! Let's go.

463
00:27:02,896 --> 00:27:03,979
Get lost!

464
00:27:05,146 --> 00:27:06,437
[officer] CSI's not done.

465
00:27:06,438 --> 00:27:09,145
Vigilante crimes. Task Force jurisdiction.

466
00:27:09,146 --> 00:27:10,228
What, are you pulling rank?

467
00:27:10,229 --> 00:27:11,313
[Matt] Let's go!

468
00:27:11,896 --> 00:27:13,354
Want me to call my friends?

469
00:27:15,688 --> 00:27:17,728
[officer] Hate these Task Force pricks.

470
00:27:17,729 --> 00:27:19,229
- [door opens]
- [doorbell dinging]

471
00:27:22,229 --> 00:27:23,479
- [door closes]
- [doorbell dinging]

472
00:27:27,271 --> 00:27:29,438
[♪ eerie music playing]

473
00:27:30,521 --> 00:27:31,688
[Matt] Jesus Christ.

474
00:27:38,688 --> 00:27:39,729
[sniffs]

475
00:27:46,354 --> 00:27:48,021
[squeaks]

476
00:27:48,771 --> 00:27:49,771
[sniffs]

477
00:27:50,604 --> 00:27:51,896
[grunts softly]

478
00:28:08,271 --> 00:28:09,478
[chuckles]

479
00:28:09,479 --> 00:28:10,771
[bell tolling]

480
00:28:16,563 --> 00:28:18,396
[♪ somber choir music playing]

481
00:28:23,479 --> 00:28:24,979
[bell tolling]

482
00:28:26,188 --> 00:28:27,188
[sighs softly]

483
00:28:49,146 --> 00:28:50,438
[shuddering breaths]

484
00:28:56,896 --> 00:28:57,979
[grunts softly]

485
00:29:07,646 --> 00:29:08,770
"Saint Lucia,

486
00:29:08,771 --> 00:29:10,771
"your beautiful name signifies light.

487
00:29:11,521 --> 00:29:14,271
"By the light of the faith
that God bestowed upon you...

488
00:29:14,854 --> 00:29:19,437
"increase and preserve this light
in my soul so that I may avoid evil,

489
00:29:19,438 --> 00:29:21,938
"be zealous in the performance
of good works...

490
00:29:22,896 --> 00:29:26,313
"And abhor nothing so much
as the darkness of evil and sin.

491
00:29:27,646 --> 00:29:28,646
"Amen."

492
00:29:29,771 --> 00:29:31,188
[seminarian] Haven't heard
that one in a long time.

493
00:29:34,479 --> 00:29:35,479
I, uh...

494
00:29:36,063 --> 00:29:37,395
I knew a boy.

495
00:29:37,396 --> 00:29:39,438
Uh, he was blind.

496
00:29:40,104 --> 00:29:42,604
Saint Lucia got him through
some tough times.

497
00:29:44,646 --> 00:29:46,021
You seem troubled, officer.

498
00:29:48,563 --> 00:29:50,563
Actually, I... I, uh,
grew up in this church.

499
00:29:52,271 --> 00:29:53,354
Haven't been back in a minute.

500
00:29:54,188 --> 00:29:55,688
[seminarian] Tell me, what--
What brings you back?

501
00:30:02,896 --> 00:30:05,146
I found that at a murder scene today.

502
00:30:07,354 --> 00:30:09,312
These tokens are available
to all our parishioners.

503
00:30:09,313 --> 00:30:10,896
So I couldn't possibly know who left this.

504
00:30:13,646 --> 00:30:15,313
[heart thumping]

505
00:30:17,021 --> 00:30:18,479
Tell me who you think...

506
00:30:19,313 --> 00:30:20,313
left it.

507
00:30:22,563 --> 00:30:24,854
[breathes deeply]

508
00:30:26,188 --> 00:30:27,229
There was a man.

509
00:30:28,229 --> 00:30:30,104
He came looking for a nun
who used to be assigned here.

510
00:30:30,938 --> 00:30:31,938
This man...

511
00:30:32,604 --> 00:30:34,146
uh, what did he want?

512
00:30:34,854 --> 00:30:36,354
He came looking for, um...

513
00:30:37,313 --> 00:30:38,813
I-- I don't know.

514
00:30:39,563 --> 00:30:41,395
Counsel. Penance.

515
00:30:41,396 --> 00:30:42,478
I told him

516
00:30:42,479 --> 00:30:45,146
I wasn't a priest yet--
He held a knife on me.

517
00:30:45,729 --> 00:30:46,729
And what did he say?

518
00:30:49,354 --> 00:30:50,646
Listen to me...

519
00:30:51,771 --> 00:30:52,771
This man...

520
00:30:54,229 --> 00:30:55,603
is a killer.

521
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:58,479
Even so, I can't turn someone over
to the police.

522
00:30:59,354 --> 00:31:00,937
His judgment is not for us to say.

523
00:31:00,938 --> 00:31:03,604
Yeah, I'm not gonna debate with you
whether or not he deserves grace...

524
00:31:04,604 --> 00:31:06,020
but I do need to find him,

525
00:31:06,021 --> 00:31:07,646
or others will die.

526
00:31:10,604 --> 00:31:11,854
What will you do...

527
00:31:13,021 --> 00:31:14,146
when you find him?

528
00:31:17,021 --> 00:31:18,021
I won't kill him.

529
00:31:23,438 --> 00:31:26,021
He told me he wakes every morning
to the sound of the church bells.

530
00:31:26,646 --> 00:31:28,896
And he watches me open the doors
for morning mass.

531
00:31:29,938 --> 00:31:31,229
Watches from where?

532
00:31:32,021 --> 00:31:33,395
His window.

533
00:31:33,396 --> 00:31:35,813
- [bell tolling]
- [indistinct chatter]

534
00:31:38,479 --> 00:31:40,021
[horn honking]

535
00:31:43,313 --> 00:31:44,354
[Dex] Let me help you with that.

536
00:31:47,646 --> 00:31:48,729
See you tomorrow.

537
00:31:49,313 --> 00:31:51,104
Such a nice boy.

538
00:31:52,979 --> 00:31:54,021
[coin clinks]

539
00:31:55,146 --> 00:31:56,478
[coins jingling]

540
00:31:56,479 --> 00:31:58,771
[truck beeping]

541
00:32:01,313 --> 00:32:02,313
[switch clicks]

542
00:32:10,229 --> 00:32:12,104
[♪ soft music playing over CD player]

543
00:32:15,063 --> 00:32:16,188
[♪ music stops]

544
00:32:17,021 --> 00:32:18,521
- [Dex grunts]
- [CD whooshing]

545
00:32:19,438 --> 00:32:20,438
[Daredevil yells]

546
00:32:21,604 --> 00:32:23,854
[both grunting]

547
00:32:25,604 --> 00:32:26,938
[both grunting]

548
00:32:34,438 --> 00:32:35,688
[both yell]

549
00:32:36,521 --> 00:32:39,146
- [grunts]
- [groans, breathes heavily]

550
00:32:42,688 --> 00:32:43,938
[Dex grunts]

551
00:32:47,021 --> 00:32:49,478
- [Daredevil yells]
- [Dex grunts]

552
00:32:49,479 --> 00:32:51,020
I'm on your side.

553
00:32:51,021 --> 00:32:52,604
[both grunting]

554
00:32:56,521 --> 00:32:58,813
[screams] What are you doing to my Tony?

555
00:33:00,396 --> 00:33:01,646
[breathing heavily]

556
00:33:04,313 --> 00:33:05,978
- [Mrs. Smithers screams]
- [Daredevil groans]

557
00:33:05,979 --> 00:33:07,353
[Dex grunts]

558
00:33:07,354 --> 00:33:08,437
Stop!

559
00:33:08,438 --> 00:33:09,645
- One good deed!
- [grunts]

560
00:33:09,646 --> 00:33:11,895
One good deed!

561
00:33:11,896 --> 00:33:13,228
Put the gun down!

562
00:33:13,229 --> 00:33:14,728
What I did--

563
00:33:14,729 --> 00:33:17,853
- What that woman had me do...
- [Daredevil] No, no, no, no, no.

564
00:33:17,854 --> 00:33:19,354
- ...to your friend...
- Don't you bring him up!

565
00:33:19,938 --> 00:33:21,603
Don't you dare bring him up!
Not like this!

566
00:33:21,604 --> 00:33:23,021
But I had to get out.

567
00:33:23,521 --> 00:33:25,063
I had to get my mind back.

568
00:33:26,063 --> 00:33:27,146
And one good deed,

569
00:33:28,396 --> 00:33:29,687
it levels the scales again.

570
00:33:29,688 --> 00:33:32,770
Oh! Uh... [chuckling]

571
00:33:32,771 --> 00:33:34,728
- All right. Okay.
- [Mrs. Smithers] No!

572
00:33:34,729 --> 00:33:35,853
What is the, uh--

573
00:33:35,854 --> 00:33:37,937
What is this, uh, one good deed?

574
00:33:37,938 --> 00:33:39,395
What is it you wanna do?

575
00:33:39,396 --> 00:33:41,271
[panting] What you wouldn't do.

576
00:33:42,521 --> 00:33:43,771
What you won't do.

577
00:33:44,479 --> 00:33:47,187
[sighs] Fisk. [exhales]

578
00:33:47,188 --> 00:33:48,312
I can't...

579
00:33:48,313 --> 00:33:50,521
I can't let you make a martyr out of him.

580
00:33:51,646 --> 00:33:53,104
I'm gonna make things right.

581
00:33:54,563 --> 00:33:55,562
I'm gonna help you.

582
00:33:55,563 --> 00:33:57,771
Please. Look, just calm down.

583
00:33:59,479 --> 00:34:00,603
I am calm.

584
00:34:00,604 --> 00:34:01,896
- [Daredevil grunts]
- [Dex grunts]

585
00:34:04,646 --> 00:34:06,021
[meows]

586
00:34:07,021 --> 00:34:09,104
- [Mrs. Smithers speaking Polish]
- [grunting]

587
00:34:11,896 --> 00:34:13,437
[scooter engine revving]

588
00:34:13,438 --> 00:34:15,021
[Daredevil grunting]

589
00:34:17,688 --> 00:34:18,978
- [Dex grunts]
- [man grunting]

590
00:34:18,979 --> 00:34:20,229
[tires screech]

591
00:34:21,563 --> 00:34:22,853
[grunts]

592
00:34:22,854 --> 00:34:24,188
[engine accelerating]

593
00:34:24,979 --> 00:34:26,313
[panting]

594
00:34:28,854 --> 00:34:31,188
[Christofi in English] My name
is Christofi Savva.

595
00:34:31,771 --> 00:34:34,438
I was the First Mate on the Northern Star.

596
00:34:35,063 --> 00:34:38,145
My Captain, Achilleo Kyriacou,

597
00:34:38,146 --> 00:34:39,645
scuttled the ship.

598
00:34:39,646 --> 00:34:42,978
We were under orders to sink the ship

599
00:34:42,979 --> 00:34:44,479
if it was ever boarded.

600
00:34:45,604 --> 00:34:47,021
Why was that?

601
00:34:48,438 --> 00:34:51,395
Because the Northern Star
was carrying weapons,

602
00:34:51,396 --> 00:34:53,271
military grade, very illegal.

603
00:34:54,396 --> 00:34:58,854
And who was the one
who ordered you to scuttle the ship?

604
00:34:59,438 --> 00:35:00,978
Achilleo called him...

605
00:35:00,979 --> 00:35:03,020
Vasillias tou Enklimatos,

606
00:35:03,021 --> 00:35:04,313
the Kingpin...

607
00:35:05,063 --> 00:35:07,146
but we knew it was the Mayor.

608
00:35:08,354 --> 00:35:09,854
There was no customs check.

609
00:35:10,563 --> 00:35:14,146
We did not have to present
a bill of lading or manifest.

610
00:35:14,771 --> 00:35:17,395
We were never registered with Coast Guard,

611
00:35:17,396 --> 00:35:18,978
Homeland Security, none of it.

612
00:35:18,979 --> 00:35:21,354
I've been to many ports
all over this world.

613
00:35:22,354 --> 00:35:24,396
In order to make that happen...

614
00:35:25,521 --> 00:35:26,854
you have to own the city.

615
00:35:27,729 --> 00:35:29,479
Uh, "own the city" is correct?

616
00:35:30,396 --> 00:35:32,396
Yeah, in this case, it just might be.

617
00:35:34,188 --> 00:35:37,853
You said you were under orders
to scuttle the Northern Star

618
00:35:37,854 --> 00:35:39,271
if it was boarded.

619
00:35:40,896 --> 00:35:42,021
Who boarded the vessel?

620
00:35:42,854 --> 00:35:43,938
Coast Guard?

621
00:35:44,729 --> 00:35:46,562
Uh, no.

622
00:35:46,563 --> 00:35:47,646
One man.

623
00:35:49,521 --> 00:35:50,688
Daredevil.

624
00:35:55,104 --> 00:35:56,728
[Kirsten] The marshals are on their way.

625
00:35:56,729 --> 00:35:58,104
They'll keep you safe.

626
00:36:03,479 --> 00:36:05,895
[indistinct chatter]

627
00:36:05,896 --> 00:36:06,979
[Daniel] Hello.

628
00:36:07,479 --> 00:36:08,895
- [BB chuckles]
- Look at that.

629
00:36:08,896 --> 00:36:10,188
Ringside, baby.

630
00:36:10,729 --> 00:36:12,145
We're gonna be so close, you and me,

631
00:36:12,146 --> 00:36:13,729
that we're gonna be
covered in sweat tonight.

632
00:36:14,854 --> 00:36:17,353
That didn't come out
how it sounded in your head.

633
00:36:17,354 --> 00:36:20,520
Did not. You know what? I was saying it,
and I sort of realized

634
00:36:20,521 --> 00:36:23,187
as it was coming out that
it wasn't really what I meant.

635
00:36:23,188 --> 00:36:24,895
- So, uh...
- Mm.

636
00:36:24,896 --> 00:36:26,354
Anyways, um...

637
00:36:26,854 --> 00:36:28,521
thank you for inviting me.

638
00:36:29,521 --> 00:36:30,520
Of course.

639
00:36:30,521 --> 00:36:32,479
Yo! You're BB.

640
00:36:33,063 --> 00:36:34,396
Like The BB Report.

641
00:36:34,938 --> 00:36:36,478
Yeah, that... that's me. You watch that?

642
00:36:36,479 --> 00:36:37,770
Everybody watches it.

643
00:36:37,771 --> 00:36:39,395
My brother, my cousin, my tía.

644
00:36:39,396 --> 00:36:40,478
Yo, they're obsessed.

645
00:36:40,479 --> 00:36:41,895
[chuckles]

646
00:36:41,896 --> 00:36:44,020
Oh, can I get a pic?
It's gonna blow their mind.

647
00:36:44,021 --> 00:36:45,271
Yeah, for sure. Come on.

648
00:36:46,979 --> 00:36:48,146
[camera shutter clicks]

649
00:36:55,354 --> 00:36:56,729
Yo, appreciate you.

650
00:36:57,271 --> 00:36:58,521
My bad.

651
00:37:00,813 --> 00:37:02,354
[♪ tense music playing]

652
00:37:07,896 --> 00:37:10,146
Didn't realize
I was on a date with a celebrity.

653
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:11,813
Come on.

654
00:37:13,021 --> 00:37:15,813
I'm not a celebrity and not a date.

655
00:37:17,063 --> 00:37:18,063
Yeah, not yet.

656
00:37:19,688 --> 00:37:21,354
[♪ "At A Disadvantage"
by Slick Naim playing]

657
00:37:24,313 --> 00:37:25,521
[siren blaring]

658
00:37:28,771 --> 00:37:29,771
[trainer] Make a fist.

659
00:37:30,646 --> 00:37:31,813
- Feel good?
- [Fisk] Yeah.

660
00:37:33,479 --> 00:37:34,728
Uh, that's not necessary.

661
00:37:34,729 --> 00:37:36,228
He'll never lay a glove on me.

662
00:37:36,229 --> 00:37:38,896
[trainer chuckles] I like
your style, Mayor.

663
00:37:41,729 --> 00:37:43,020
Anything?

664
00:37:43,021 --> 00:37:46,145
No. We have men on rooftops, subways,

665
00:37:46,146 --> 00:37:47,645
every entrance, and exit.

666
00:37:47,646 --> 00:37:50,520
Inside's covered, too.
We have Task Force in plainclothes

667
00:37:50,521 --> 00:37:52,603
and uniforms lugging serious firepower,

668
00:37:52,604 --> 00:37:53,854
so nothing's getting in.

669
00:37:54,563 --> 00:37:56,146
We'll need an entrance cleared.

670
00:37:58,354 --> 00:38:00,063
Preferably, the front doors.

671
00:38:02,396 --> 00:38:04,103
Sir, uh, I don't think tying yourself

672
00:38:04,104 --> 00:38:05,896
- to the stake is a very...
- [phone vibrating]

673
00:38:07,813 --> 00:38:09,021
...good idea.

674
00:38:10,438 --> 00:38:12,271
[Fisk] Looks like
you have somewhere to be.

675
00:38:16,688 --> 00:38:17,979
I'm not going anywhere...

676
00:38:18,479 --> 00:38:20,896
especially if you wanna
dangle yourself out as bait.

677
00:38:21,479 --> 00:38:22,853
Buck...

678
00:38:22,854 --> 00:38:23,938
go.

679
00:38:25,479 --> 00:38:27,313
We can't have any loose ends.

680
00:38:29,063 --> 00:38:30,271
[Buck sighs]

681
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:35,520
[Fisk sighs]

682
00:38:35,521 --> 00:38:37,021
Don't worry, sir. Me and North got it.

683
00:38:37,979 --> 00:38:40,188
[rapper] ♪ I was working,
I couldn't understand it ♪

684
00:38:40,854 --> 00:38:43,228
♪ I was hurting, I was in a panic ♪

685
00:38:43,229 --> 00:38:45,688
♪ See, I felt like
I ain't meet the standards ♪

686
00:38:46,396 --> 00:38:48,145
♪ But yet, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

687
00:38:48,146 --> 00:38:49,228
[all cheering]

688
00:38:49,229 --> 00:38:51,228
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

689
00:38:51,229 --> 00:38:56,312
♪ Yes, I made it at a disadvantage ♪

690
00:38:56,313 --> 00:38:58,645
- [Daniel] All right. I got prezzies.
- [BB] Ooh.

691
00:38:58,646 --> 00:39:00,770
I thought you're a foam finger kinda lady.

692
00:39:00,771 --> 00:39:01,978
[scoffs] I'm not.

693
00:39:01,979 --> 00:39:03,812
[Daniel] And there you go.

694
00:39:03,813 --> 00:39:05,187
Oh. Thank you.

695
00:39:05,188 --> 00:39:06,437
[Daniel] Look at this.

696
00:39:06,438 --> 00:39:07,854
Bobblehead Fisk, uh?

697
00:39:08,854 --> 00:39:10,562
- Very realistic.
- [Sheila chuckles]

698
00:39:10,563 --> 00:39:11,770
Look at that.

699
00:39:11,771 --> 00:39:13,438
Pure class.

700
00:39:14,104 --> 00:39:15,396
I hope you got the discount.

701
00:39:17,063 --> 00:39:18,354
There's a discount?

702
00:39:19,354 --> 00:39:20,354
Shit.

703
00:39:25,229 --> 00:39:27,395
Ladies and gentlemen,

704
00:39:27,396 --> 00:39:29,062
proud New Yorkers,

705
00:39:29,063 --> 00:39:32,020
welcome to Scrappin' In The Kitchen,

706
00:39:32,021 --> 00:39:37,603
benefiting the New York Born Again
revitalization project.

707
00:39:37,604 --> 00:39:40,853
The main event
will consist of three rounds.

708
00:39:40,854 --> 00:39:43,395
Winner determined by knockout,

709
00:39:43,396 --> 00:39:46,103
TKO, or points.

710
00:39:46,104 --> 00:39:48,603
Now, get out of your seats,

711
00:39:48,604 --> 00:39:52,187
clap your hands, and welcome--

712
00:39:52,188 --> 00:39:53,770
In purple trunks,

713
00:39:53,771 --> 00:39:56,645
weighing in at 235 pounds

714
00:39:56,646 --> 00:39:59,895
with a professional record
of thirty-two and two,

715
00:39:59,896 --> 00:40:03,687
- Mike "The Matterhorn" Melendez!
- [booing]

716
00:40:03,688 --> 00:40:07,312
And in the white corner,

717
00:40:07,313 --> 00:40:10,353
our hometown hero of Hell's Kitchen,

718
00:40:10,354 --> 00:40:12,062
wearing white trunks,

719
00:40:12,063 --> 00:40:15,187
weighing in at 325 pounds,

720
00:40:15,188 --> 00:40:18,145
with no professional boxing record,

721
00:40:18,146 --> 00:40:23,103
Mayor Wilson "Wildcard" Fisk!

722
00:40:23,104 --> 00:40:25,270
[all cheering]

723
00:40:25,271 --> 00:40:27,396
[♪ dramatic music playing]

724
00:40:27,854 --> 00:40:29,728
- [man 1] Yeah!
- [man 2] Boo!

725
00:40:29,729 --> 00:40:30,854
[all applauding]

726
00:40:51,896 --> 00:40:54,562
- [man 3] Boo!
- Yeah! [chanting] Fisk! Fisk! Fisk!

727
00:40:54,563 --> 00:40:56,728
Fisk! Fisk! Fisk! Fisk!

728
00:40:56,729 --> 00:40:58,146
Fisk!

729
00:41:11,396 --> 00:41:12,812
[referee] I want a clean fight.

730
00:41:12,813 --> 00:41:14,312
Nothing below the belt.

731
00:41:14,313 --> 00:41:16,687
Obey my commands.
Defend yourselves at all times.

732
00:41:16,688 --> 00:41:17,938
Touch gloves.

733
00:41:19,938 --> 00:41:21,313
[thuds]

734
00:41:25,479 --> 00:41:26,479
[all cheering]

735
00:41:27,688 --> 00:41:29,021
[man 4] Yeah!

736
00:41:31,479 --> 00:41:33,271
[♪ dramatic music continues]

737
00:41:51,021 --> 00:41:52,270
[bell dings]

738
00:41:52,271 --> 00:41:53,604
[Fisk breathing raggedly]

739
00:41:56,063 --> 00:41:57,813
- [Fisk grunts]
- [groans]

740
00:42:00,896 --> 00:42:04,021
[grunts, groans]

741
00:42:06,063 --> 00:42:07,520
Yeah! Yes!

742
00:42:07,521 --> 00:42:08,687
Let's go!

743
00:42:08,688 --> 00:42:10,895
That what you want? Fine!

744
00:42:10,896 --> 00:42:12,146
[Fisk yells]

745
00:42:19,021 --> 00:42:20,604
[tires screech]

746
00:42:25,813 --> 00:42:27,229
- [gunshots]
- [officers grunt]

747
00:42:27,938 --> 00:42:30,646
[both grunting]

748
00:42:35,729 --> 00:42:36,813
Hello, Mr. Savva.

749
00:42:40,521 --> 00:42:41,896
- [both grunting]
- [all cheering]

750
00:42:42,896 --> 00:42:44,063
[heavy breathing]

751
00:42:46,313 --> 00:42:47,979
[Fisk grunting]

752
00:42:49,063 --> 00:42:51,020
- [Mike groans]
- [bell dinging]

753
00:42:51,021 --> 00:42:53,478
[Fisk yelling]

754
00:42:53,479 --> 00:42:55,813
- Yeah! Yes! Yes!
- Oh, my God.

755
00:42:57,438 --> 00:42:59,104
[all cheering]

756
00:43:01,063 --> 00:43:03,104
[camera shutter clicking]

757
00:43:04,188 --> 00:43:06,271
[grunts, breathes heavily]

758
00:43:11,896 --> 00:43:13,813
Christofi's been taken care of.

759
00:43:14,771 --> 00:43:15,771
All right.

760
00:43:22,104 --> 00:43:24,688
- [breathes deeply]
- [bell dinging]

761
00:43:27,396 --> 00:43:29,229
[all cheering]

762
00:43:31,271 --> 00:43:33,313
[both grunting]

763
00:43:36,354 --> 00:43:37,812
[woman] Yeah!

764
00:43:37,813 --> 00:43:38,895
Yeah!

765
00:43:38,896 --> 00:43:41,188
[all cheering]

766
00:43:42,021 --> 00:43:43,646
[both grunting]

767
00:43:48,854 --> 00:43:51,063
[Fisk breathing heavily]

768
00:43:53,813 --> 00:43:55,520
[grunts softly]

769
00:43:55,521 --> 00:43:57,021
[straining]

770
00:44:00,479 --> 00:44:01,521
[Fisk breathing heavily]

771
00:44:02,021 --> 00:44:03,771
[Fisk grunts]

772
00:44:06,396 --> 00:44:08,938
[grunts, yells]

773
00:44:11,646 --> 00:44:13,563
[thuds]

774
00:44:14,604 --> 00:44:15,979
- [yells]
- [groans]

775
00:44:16,729 --> 00:44:18,396
[blood splattering]

776
00:44:24,521 --> 00:44:26,145
[woman screams] Oh!

777
00:44:26,146 --> 00:44:27,604
[people murmuring softly]

778
00:44:38,646 --> 00:44:40,188
[bell dinging]

779
00:44:46,813 --> 00:44:48,813
[all applauding, cheering]

780
00:45:00,646 --> 00:45:02,104
[bell dinging]

781
00:45:03,146 --> 00:45:04,604
[all cheering]

782
00:45:10,104 --> 00:45:11,103
Yeah!

783
00:45:11,104 --> 00:45:12,229
Oh, my God.

784
00:45:13,229 --> 00:45:16,271
- [camera shutter clicking]
- [cheering continues]

785
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:33,646
You came.

786
00:45:34,438 --> 00:45:35,646
With a win.

787
00:45:36,521 --> 00:45:38,228
- I told you not to come.
- Kiss me.

